    org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.helpers.DatamodelConverter.getOptionLanguageFilter()
    Use DatamodelFilter Returns the (possibly empty) set of language codes that are used to filter data while copying it, or null if no such filter is configured (default). If not equal to null, only terms in the given language will be copied.
    org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.helpers.DatamodelConverter.getOptionPropertyFilter()
    Use DatamodelFilter Returns the (possibly empty) set of PropertyIdValue objects that are used to filter statements while copying data, or null if no such filter is configured (default). If not equal to null, only statements using the given properties will be copied.
    org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.helpers.DatamodelConverter.getOptionSiteLinkFilter()
    Use DatamodelFilter Returns the (possibly empty) set of site keys that are used to filter SiteLink objects while copying data, or null if no such filter is configured (default). If not equal to null, only site links for the given sites will be copied.
    org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.helpers.DatamodelConverter.hasOptionDeepCopy()
    Shallow copy is not supported anymore Returns true if objects will be copied by deep copy, replacing all subobjects recursively. This is the default.
    org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.helpers.DatamodelConverter.hasOptionDeepCopyReferences()
    Support for filtering references is going to be removed from DatamodelConverter Returns true if references will be copied when creating a deep copy of statements. This is the default. The setting has no effect when shallow copies are used.
    org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.helpers.DatamodelConverter.setOptionDeepCopy​(boolean)
    Shallow copy is not supported anymore Sets the value of the deep copy option. If true, subobjects of objects will be copied recursively.
    org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.helpers.DatamodelConverter.setOptionDeepCopyReferences​(boolean)
    Support for filtering references is going to be removed from DatamodelConverter Sets the value of the deep copy references option. If true, references will be copied when creating a deep copy of statements.
    org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.helpers.DatamodelConverter.setOptionFilter​(DocumentDataFilter)
    Use DatamodelFilter Replaces the current filter settings with the given ones. Future changes to the settings will take effect (a reference is used, not a full copy).
    org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.helpers.DatamodelConverter.setOptionLanguageFilter​(Set<String>)
    Use DatamodelFilter Sets the (possibly empty) set of language codes that are used to filter data while copying it. Setting this to null disables this filter (this is the default). If not equal to null, only terms in the given language will be copied.

    The language filter is not applied to monolingual text values in statements. Only labels, descriptions, and aliases are filtered.
    org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.helpers.DatamodelConverter.setOptionPropertyFilter​(Set<PropertyIdValue>)
    Use DatamodelFilter Sets the (possibly empty) set of PropertyIdValue objects that are used to filter statements while copying data. Setting this to null disables this filter (this is the default). If not equal to null, only statements using the given properties will be copied.

    The property filter is not applied to qualifiers and references in statements. Only the main property of statements is filtered.
    org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.helpers.DatamodelConverter.setOptionSiteLinkFilter​(Set<String>)
    Use DatamodelFilter Sets the (possibly empty) set of site keys that are used to filter SiteLink objects while copying data. Setting this to null disables this filter (this is the default). If not equal to null, only site links for the given sites will be copied.
    org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.interfaces.ItemDocument.getItemId()
    Use ItemDocument.getEntityId() Return the ID of the item that the data refers to. The result is the same as that of EntityDocument.getEntityId(), but declared with a more specific result type.
    org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.interfaces.PropertyDocument.getPropertyId()
    Use PropertyDocument.getEntityId() Return the ID of the property that the data refers to. The result is the same as that of EntityDocument.getEntityId(), but declared with a more specific result type.
    org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.interfaces.Snak.getValue()
    Only ValueSnak has a value. Get the Value of this Snak, or null if the snak has no specified value.
    org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.interfaces.StatementDocument.findStatementDatatypeIdValue​(PropertyIdValue)
    DatatypeIdValue is not allowed as snak value Returns the unique DatatypeIdValue for the given property, or null if there are zero or many such values given in statements for this property.

    This is a convenience method for accessing the data that can be obtained via StatementDocument.getStatementGroups().
    org.wikidata.wdtk.dumpfiles.DumpProcessingController.processMostRecentDailyDump()

    org.wikidata.wdtk.dumpfiles.DumpProcessingController.processMostRecentDump​(DumpContentType, MwDumpFileProcessor)
    Use DumpProcessingController.getMostRecentDump(DumpContentType) and DumpProcessingController.processDump(MwDumpFile) instead; method will vanish in WDTK 0.5
